The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Long hours equal frayed tempers

 Jaidip Moitra: Traffic personnel are often rude and indifferent to public problems.

 Most traffic sergeants and constables work for long hours at a stretch. They work in a harsh atmosphere, braving the dust and smoke. Their attitude is a reflection of their physical hardship. However, it is not desirable that they be indifferent when approached for help.

 We have already started a motivation course in the Police Training School. We also run a short course by which constables are trained to deal with such situations.




